<h2 id="_1_info_total_revenue_development">1. 1) Info: total revenue development</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This statistic shows the <strong>number of sales orders</strong> and the <strong>revenue in Euro</strong> for a certain <strong>time span</strong> that was previously set. Default setting for the time span: revenue of the <strong>last 10 days</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_2_details_about_the_statistic">2. 2) Details about the statistic</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>number of sales orders</strong> and the <strong>revenue in Euro</strong> will be displayed for each day within the selected <strong>time span</strong>. If no sales orders are available, then the point <strong>0</strong> will be displayed on the line graph and no column will be displayed behind it. The <strong>number of sales orders</strong> and the corresponding <strong>date</strong> will be displayed as information in a mouseover. Furthermore, a second color will display the <strong>revenue</strong> that was generated by the particular number of sales orders (see image 1). In this statistic you can see, e.g. when a few sales orders generated a large amount of revenue and therefore many sales orders generated only a small amount of revenue.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock warning">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-warning" title="Warning"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title"><strong>Item bundles</strong></div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>number of returned items from item bundles</strong> will be analyzed. However, the corresponding <u>revenue will not</u>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title"><strong>Show details (mouseover)</strong></div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Point your <strong>cursor</strong> at one of the elements in the statistic in order to see <strong>details</strong> about that particular element.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Tip</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In image 1, you can see that <strong>9 sales orders</strong> generated a total <strong>revenue</strong> of <strong>846.20 Euros</strong> on <strong>October 25th, 2012</strong>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title"><strong>Number of sales orders</strong></div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Returns</strong> and <strong>credit notes</strong> are not included in the <strong>number of sales orders</strong>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
